\begin_layout Standard
Projecting onto the translational modes yields the reduced system.
 We introduce the following quantities:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
\begin_inset Argument 1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Interaction functional and coefficients
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "def:interaction"

\end_inset

 The 
\emph on
interaction functional
\emph default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
Q_{R}(z)=-\sigma\,\bigl\langle\partial_{z/|z|}u_{R}(\cdot-z),\,u_{R}^{2p+1}\bigr\rangle_{L^{2}}.
\]

\end_inset

The 
\emph on
minimum inter-peak distance
\emph default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula $m_{R}=\min\{|z_{j}(R)-z_{i}(R)|:i\neq j\}$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\emph on
interaction coefficients
\emph default
 are 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\alpha_{ki}=\frac{Q_{R}(|z_{k}-z_{i}|)}{Q_{R}(m_{R})},\quad\text{satisfying }0\leq\alpha_{ki}\leq1,\label{eq:alpha-def}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}=1$
\end_inset

 precisely when 
\begin_inset Formula $|z_{k}-z_{i}|=m_{R}$
\end_inset

 (nearest neighbors).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
\begin_inset Argument 1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Overall interaction strength
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "def:chi"

\end_inset

 The 
\emph on
overall interaction strength
\emph default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\chi=\frac{2\,Q_{R}(m_{R})}{\norm{u_{R}}_{L^{2}}^{2}\,R^{4}\,m_{R}}>0.\label{eq:chi-def}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

This is a single positive scalar that captures the magnitude of the inter-peak interaction relative to the Hessian restoring force.
 It is 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 equal to any individual 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}$
\end_inset

;
 rather,
 the force on peak 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 from peak 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 has magnitude 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}\chi$
\end_inset

.
 
