\begin_layout Corollary
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "cor:unstable"

\end_inset

 The peak positions satisfy 
\begin_inset Formula $\operatorname{span}\{y_{1},\ldots,y_{M}\}\subseteq U$
\end_inset

,
 where 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U=\operatorname{span}\bigl\{\boldsymbol{r}\in\R^{n}:\HV(x_{0})\boldsymbol{r}=\lambda\boldsymbol{r},\;\lambda<0\bigr\}
\]

\end_inset

is the unstable subspace of 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV(x_{0})$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Write 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}=y_{i}^{U}+y_{i}^{S}$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}^{U}\in U$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}^{S}\in U^{\perp}$
\end_inset

.
 Applying the orthogonal projection 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{S}$
\end_inset

 onto 
\begin_inset Formula $U^{\perp}$
\end_inset

 to the algebraic system
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

(2.4) gives 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\HV\,y_{i}^{S}=\chi\sum_{k\in N_{i}}\alpha_{ki}\bigl(y_{k}^{S}-y_{i}^{S}\bigr),\label{eq:projected-stable}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

since 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV$
\end_inset

 preserves both 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U^{\perp}$
\end_inset

 (they are eigenspaces) and 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{S}(y_{k}-y_{i})=y_{k}^{S}-y_{i}^{S}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Now take the inner product of
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:projected-stable"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}^{S}$
\end_inset

 and sum over
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sum_{i=1}^{M}\ip{y_{i}^{S}}{\HV\,y_{i}^{S}}=\chi\sum_{i=1}^{M}\sum_{k\in N_{i}}\alpha_{ki}\,\ip{y_{i}^{S}}{y_{k}^{S}-y_{i}^{S}}.
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
Left side.

\series default
 Since 
\begin_inset Formula $\HV\big|_{U^{\perp}}$
\end_inset

 has all eigenvalues in 
\begin_inset Formula $[\lambda_{\min}^{S},\infty)$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{\min}^{S}>0$
\end_inset

 (Hypothesis
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

V4 places the peaks at a strict local maximum,
 so eigenvalues in directions 
\emph on
not
\emph default
 used by the peaks are positive),
 we have 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{LHS}\;\geq\;\lambda_{\min}^{S}\sum_{i}\abs{y_{i}^{S}}^{2}.
\]

\end_inset


\series bold
Right side.

\series default
 Each nearest-neighbor edge 
\begin_inset Formula $\{i,k\}$
\end_inset

 contributes the ordered pairs 
\begin_inset Formula $(i,k)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $(k,i)$
\end_inset

.
 Using the symmetry 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}=\alpha_{ik}$
\end_inset

 (since 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{R}$
\end_inset

 depends only on 
\begin_inset Formula $\abs{z_{k}-z_{i}}$
\end_inset

),
 the contribution of each edge is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\alpha_{ki}\Bigl[\ip{y_{i}^{S}}{y_{k}^{S}-y_{i}^{S}}+\ip{y_{k}^{S}}{y_{i}^{S}-y_{k}^{S}}\Bigr] & =-\alpha_{ki}\abs{y_{k}^{S}-y_{i}^{S}}^{2}.
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Summing over all edges:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\text{RHS}=-\chi\!\!\sum_{\{i,k\}\in\text{edges}}\alpha_{ki}\abs{y_{k}^{S}-y_{i}^{S}}^{2}\;\leq\;0,
\]

\end_inset

since 
\begin_inset Formula $\chi>0$
\end_inset

 and every 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{ki}\geq0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
Combining:
 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{\min}^{S}\sum_{i}\abs{y_{i}^{S}}^{2}\leq0$
\end_inset

.
 Because 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{\min}^{S}>0$
\end_inset

,
 we conclude 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}^{S}=0$
\end_inset

 for every 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,\ldots,M$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

