\begin_layout Section
Kernel Resolution and Gauge-Fixing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sec:gauge"

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%% ==================================================================
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The four-dimensional kernel 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

 prevents a direct application of the implicit function theorem (IFT) to continue solutions from 
\begin_inset Formula $R=0$
\end_inset

 to 
\begin_inset Formula $R>0$
\end_inset

.
 Following the iterative kernel decomposition methodology of
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "KirrNatarajan2018"
literal "false"

\end_inset

,
 we decompose the reduced system into projections perpendicular and parallel to 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Projection decomposition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:projections"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For 
\begin_inset Formula $w\in\Omega$
\end_inset

,
 define 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P_{w}F(\delta y,R)=\sum_{i}\ip{w_{i}}{F_{i}(\delta y,R)}.
\]

\end_inset

We decompose 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 into its perpendicular projection 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{\perp}F$
\end_inset

 (a vector-valued system on 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega^{\perp}$
\end_inset

) and parallel projections 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{w}F$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $w$
\end_inset

 ranging over a basis of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At 
\begin_inset Formula $(\delta y^{0},0)$
\end_inset

,
 the linearizations are:
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
D_{\delta y}P_{\perp}F(\delta y^{0},0)[\delta w] & =P_{\perp}\sum_{k\in N_{i}}\ip{\delta w_{k}-\delta w_{i}}{y_{k}-y_{i}}\,\tilde{\alpha}_{ik}(0)\,\chi\,(y_{k}-y_{i}),\label{eq:DPperp}\\
D_{\delta y}P_{w}F(\delta y^{0},0)[\delta w] & =\sum_{i}\Bigl[\ip{w_{i}}{\HV\delta w_{i}}+\sum_{k\in N_{i}}\tilde{\alpha}_{ki}(0)\bigl(\ip{w_{i}}{\delta y_{k}^{0}-\delta y_{i}^{0}}\ip{y_{k}-y_{i}}{\delta w_{k}-\delta w_{i}}\nonumber \\
 & \quad\qquad-\ip{w_{i}}{\delta w_{k}-\delta w_{i}}\bigr)\Bigr].\label{eq:DPpar}
\end{align}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Gauge-fixing constraints
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:gauge-fix"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To break the translational and rotational symmetries,
 we impose:
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
(G1)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\delta y_{1}\perp\boldsymbol{r}_{1}$
\end_inset

 (the first peak has no displacement along 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{r}_{1}$
\end_inset

),
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Argument item:1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
(G2)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $(\delta y_{3}-\delta y_{2})\parallel\boldsymbol{r}_{1}$
\end_inset

 (the base of the triangle displaces only along 
\begin_inset Formula $\boldsymbol{r}_{1}$
\end_inset

).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These two scalar constraints remove 2 of the 4 kernel directions (one translation component and the rotation mode),
 leaving a 2-dimensional residual kernel corresponding to the remaining translation and the breathing mode.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Rotational equivariance at 
\begin_inset Formula $R=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:equivariance"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proposition
\begin_inset Argument 1
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Family structure at 
\begin_inset Formula $R=0$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop:family"

\end_inset

 The one-parameter family of equilateral triangle configurations 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}(\theta)=R(\theta)y_{i}'$
\end_inset

,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta\in[\theta_{\min},\theta_{\max}]$
\end_inset

 (the admissible 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

-range from Proposition
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop:admissibility"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

),
 generates a corresponding family of solutions 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta y^{0}(\theta)$
\end_inset

 of the system 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{i}(\delta y,0)=0$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
For each admissible 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

,
 the base configuration 
\begin_inset Formula $y_{i}(\theta)$
\end_inset

 satisfies the algebraic system
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:algebraic"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\theta$
\end_inset

-dependent coefficients 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{12}(\theta),\alpha_{13}(\theta),\alpha_{23}(\theta)$
\end_inset

 from
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:alpha12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

–
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:alpha23"
plural "false"
caps "false"
